name: Abir BHowmik
bio: Sarah Jenkins is a classically trained soprano with over 10 years of experience performing at weddings, galas, and corporate events. She studied at Juilliard and has performed with the New York Philharmonic. Her warm, powerful voice brings emotional depth to every performance, specializing in classical arias, contemporary ballads, and custom wedding compositions. She is perfect for elegant ceremonies and upscale events.

name: Rita Choudhury
bio: Marcus Rivera is Chicago's top DJ with 8 years of experience spinning at corporate events, nightclubs, and high-profile parties. Known for his seamless transitions and ability to read the crowd, Marcus blends EDM, hip-hop, and top 40 hits to create unforgettable experiences. He has performed at Fortune 500 company events, rooftop parties, and music festivals. His professional-grade equipment ensures crisp sound at any venue.

name: Anika Patel
bio: Anika Patel is a versatile dancer based in Los Angeles who specializes in Bollywood fusion and contemporary dance. With 12 years of training and 6 years of professional performance, she has graced stages at cultural festivals, Bollywood events, weddings, and brand activations. Her choreography blends classical Indian dance forms with modern western styles, making her performances visually stunning and culturally rich. Available for solo performances, group choreography, and dance workshops.

name: Soumen Saha
bio: James O'Brien is an acclaimed jazz guitarist from Atlanta with a soulful approach to blues and jazz. He has performed at renowned venues like Jazz at Lincoln Center and has shared stages with Grammy-winning artists. James specializes in creating the perfect musical ambiance for upscale restaurants, wedding receptions, cocktail hours, and corporate dinners. His smooth, melodic playing style is perfect for background music that enhances the atmosphere without overwhelming conversation.

name: Ash Chatterjee
bio: Elena Vasquez is a celebrated event and portrait photographer based in San Francisco with a decade of experience capturing life's most important moments. Her work has been featured in Vogue, The Knot, and Forbes. Elena's signature style combines candid storytelling with editorial precision, delivering images that are both emotionally resonant and visually striking. She specializes in weddings, corporate events, product launches, and executive portraiture. Her post-processing style is timeless and elegant.

name: Bushu Sen
bio: David Kim is a classically trained pianist who graduated summa cum laude from the Seattle Conservatory of Music. He performs across a wide range of styles including classical, jazz, and contemporary, making him extremely versatile for any event. David is a favorite for wedding ceremonies, cocktail receptions, charity galas, and intimate dinner parties. His ability to play both composed pieces and improvise on request makes every performance unique and tailored to the occasion.

name: Priya Sharma
bio: Priya Sharma is a visionary live event painter who transforms blank canvases into masterpieces right before your guests' eyes. Based in Houston, she has performed live painting at over 200 weddings, corporate events, and art galas. Her specialty is creating stunning portraits and abstract pieces during the event itself, providing both entertainment and a lasting keepsake. Her work spans oil, acrylic, and watercolor, and she often incorporates elements requested by the client to make each piece truly personal.

name: Tony Roy
bio: Tony Marchetti is Miami's hottest DJ, known for his electrifying Latin mixes and ability to turn any gathering into a full-blown fiesta. With 10 years of experience DJing at South Beach's top clubs and luxury resort events, Tony specializes in Latin, reggaeton, salsa, and mainstream dance music. He has headlined at Art Basel Miami, exclusive yacht parties, and multi-day resort events. Tony's energy is infectious and his song selection is always on point, guaranteed to keep the dance floor packed all night.

name: Rachel Thompson
bio: Rachel Thompson is a powerhouse vocalist from the musical heartland of New Orleans. Her voice carries the rich tradition of jazz, blues, and gospel that defines the city's soul. Rachel has performed at the New Orleans Jazz & Heritage Festival, Essence Festival, and hundreds of private events. She specializes in creating intimate, soulful performances that move audiences to their core. Whether it's a smoky jazz lounge ambiance or an uplifting gospel-inspired wedding ceremony, Rachel brings authenticity and raw emotion to every note.

name: Carlos Mendez
bio: Carlos Mendez is a world-class magician and mentalist based in Dallas who has baffled audiences across the globe. His show combines grand stage illusions with intimate mentalism to create an experience that leaves audiences speechless. Carlos has performed at TEDx conferences, Fortune 500 corporate events, private celebrity parties, and international magic conventions. His act is polished, professional, and suitable for all audiences. He customizes each show to incorporate brand messaging or personal themes, making him uniquely valuable for corporate entertainment.

name: Zoe Anderson
bio: Zoe Anderson is a professionally trained ballet and contemporary dancer from Chicago with 15 years of performance experience. She trained at the Royal Academy of Dance in London and has performed with the Chicago Ballet Company. Zoe specializes in creating breathtaking performance pieces for weddings, galas, and corporate events. Her aerial silk performances are particularly popular for upscale events looking for a showstopping moment. She also offers choreography services for wedding first dances and custom performances.

name: Nathan Brooks
bio: Nathan Brooks is a Nashville-based country and folk singer-songwriter with an authentic, heartfelt performance style. He has released three studio albums and performed at country music festivals across the South. Nathan's warm baritone voice and masterful acoustic guitar playing create an intimate atmosphere perfect for outdoor weddings, barn events, and country-themed parties. He writes original songs on request and can perform covers from classic country to modern hits. His genuine love for storytelling through music resonates deeply with audiences.

name: Isabella Chen
bio: Isabella Chen is a New York-based fashion and event photographer whose work has appeared in Harper's Bazaar, Elle, and numerous international campaigns. With a sharp editorial eye and a passion for capturing authentic moments, Isabella brings a high-fashion sensibility to every shoot. Her event photography clients range from luxury fashion house launches to intimate gallery openings. She uses state-of-the-art equipment and delivers a signature clean, luminous aesthetic. Her fast turnaround and meticulous retouching make her a top choice for high-profile events.

name: Darius Williams
bio: Darius Williams is a Detroit-born musician and band leader who brings the raw energy of Motor City music to every stage. Specializing in R&B, funk, and soul, Darius performs as a saxophonist and vocalist, and leads a tight 5-piece band that can be hired as a complete package. His live performances are high-energy spectacles that get every audience member on their feet. Darius has performed at major Detroit events, opened for touring national acts, and is a sought-after session musician for studio recordings.

name: Sophia Laurent
bio: Sophia Laurent is a New Orleans-based watercolor artist who brings the magic of live painting to events of all kinds. Her delicate, luminous style captures the emotion and atmosphere of special moments in real time. Sophia has created live paintings at weddings, anniversaries, corporate retreats, and art festivals throughout the Gulf Coast. She works with extraordinary speed and detail, often completing a full-size canvas during a 3-4 hour event. Each painting becomes a cherished heirloom for clients, making her services uniquely meaningful and memorable.

name: Alex Turner
bio: Alex Turner is a Las Vegas-based comedian and professional emcee with a sharp wit and crowd-commanding presence. He has performed at casinos, comedy clubs, corporate award ceremonies, and private events throughout the country. Alex specializes in clean corporate comedy and audience-interactive shows that keep energy high throughout any event. He is a gifted improviser who adapts his material to the specific audience and occasion, ensuring every performance feels fresh, personalized, and hilariously funny. He is also available as a full-event host and emcee.

name: Maya Paul
bio: Maya Johnson is an Atlanta-based gospel and R&B vocalist with a voice that moves mountains. She has performed at mega-churches, music festivals, and high-profile weddings across the Southeast. Maya's powerful, Spirit-filled performances have moved thousands of people to tears and inspired standing ovations. She is equally at home delivering a tender wedding ballad or leading a full gospel choir performance. Maya also works as a session vocalist for studio recordings and has contributed to multiple Grammy-nominated albums.

name: Leo Fontaine
bio: Leo Fontaine is a New Orleans brass band musician and jazz trumpeter who embodies the spirit of the city's legendary music culture. He leads the Fontaine Brass Band, a 6-piece ensemble specializing in New Orleans second line, jazz funerals, and street parade entertainment. Leo has marched and performed at Mardi Gras, Jazz Fest, and countless weddings, parties, and corporate events. His music brings an unparalleled festive energy that transforms any gathering into a joyful celebration. Perfect for outdoor events, parades, and anyone who wants an unforgettable musical experience.

name: Chloe Park
bio: Chloe Park is a dynamic Los Angeles-based dancer and choreographer specializing in K-Pop and hip-hop styles. With training from top studios in Seoul and LA, she brings a cutting-edge, high-energy performance style that is enormously popular at brand events, music festivals, and entertainment showcases. Chloe has choreographed music videos for emerging artists, performed at K-Pop conventions, and regularly appears at major entertainment company events. Her powerful stage presence and precision technique make every performance a crowd favorite.

name: Oliver Hayes
bio: Oliver Hayes is a Boston-based documentary and fine art photographer known for his distinctive black and white style and photojournalistic approach to event photography. He studied at the School of Visual Arts and has exhibited in galleries across New England. Oliver's work captures the unscripted, genuine moments that tell the real story of an event. He is equally talented with color and monochrome work, and his wedding photography in particular is celebrated for its timeless elegance and emotional authenticity. Oliver is a storyteller with a camera.
